@startuml SabaGroupBetting_MainFlow
!theme plain
title Match Monitor Saba Group Betting - Main Business Flow (Updated 2025-11-19)

start

floating note : PHASE 1 - STAGING (Shared with all rules)

:Insert Ticket Detail;
note right
    **Staging Tables:**
    - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaLive
    - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaNonLive
    
    **Key Fields:**
    - SequenceID (auto-increment)
    - TransID, CustID, CTSCustID
    - MatchID, ScoreDiff, BettypeID, BetID, Betteam
    - SportType, LeagueGroupID
    - Stake, TransDateToSecond
    - GroupID (initially 0)
end note

floating note : PHASE 2 - PROCESSING (Saba-Specific)

:Job Triggered (HTTP POST);
note right
    Endpoint: /api/matchmonitor/MatchMonitorProcessRuleSabaGroupBettingLive
    or: /api/matchmonitor/MatchMonitorProcessRuleSabaGroupBettingNonLive
    Parameter: numberOfThread
end note

:MatchMonitorJobService.ProcessRuleSabaGroupBetting(isLive, numberOfThread);

:GetMatchRuleSabaGB(isLive);
:Call SP: CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_Get(isLive);
note right
    **Database:** CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)
    **SP Name:** CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_Get
    
    **Returns:**
    - MaxSequenceID (OUT parameter)
    - CTSCustomerList (for mapping dictionary)
    - MatchStagingList (grouped matches)
    
    **Tables Used:**
    - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaLive
    - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaNonLive
    - MatchMonitorRuleSetting
    - SystemParameter
end note

partition "=== CREATE MAPPING DICTIONARY ===" {
    :Extract CTSCustomerList;
    note right
        From SP result:
        SELECT DISTINCT CustID, CTSCustID
        FROM MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSaba[Live/NonLive]
        WHERE SequenceID <= MaxSequenceID
        
        Example Result:
        [
            { CustID: 101, CTSCustID: 5001 },
            { CustID: 102, CTSCustID: 5002 },
            { CustID: 103, CTSCustID: 5003 }
        ]
    end note
    
    :Create MappingCustDictionary;
    note right
        **KEY SABA FEATURE!**
        
        MappingCustDictionary = CTSCustomerList
            .Select(x => new { x.CustID, x.CTSCustID })
            .Distinct()
            .ToDictionary(x => x.CustID, x => x.CTSCustID);
        
        Type: IReadOnlyDictionary<int, int>
        
        Example Result:
        {
            101: 5001,
            102: 5002,
            103: 5003
        }
        
        Purpose:
        - Map Saba CustID to CTS internal CTSCustID
        - Used in association detection
        - Essential for Saba platform integration
    end note
    
    :Dictionary Ready;
}

:Group Matches;
note right
    Group by: MatchID, ScoreDiff, BettypeID, BetID, Betteam
    Filter by:
    - TotalStake >= RuleSetting.TotalStake
    - COUNT(DISTINCT CustID) > 1
    - SUM(CustStake) >= TotalStake
end note

if (Has Matches?) then (yes)
    :Parallel Processing Setup;
    note right
        AsParallel()
        WithDegreeOfParallelism(numberOfThread)
    end note
    
    partition "Process Single Match (Per Thread)" {
        :Get Process Service Instance;
        note right
            _ruleSabaGBService.GetInstanceProcessSabaGBService()
            Returns: MMRuleSabaGBProcessService
        end note
        
        :PrepareProcess(matchInfo, isLive, mappingCustDictionary);
        note right
            **Pass MappingCustDictionary!**
            
            This is KEY difference from standard:
            - Standard: Pass AssociationSettings
            - Saba: Pass MappingCustDictionary
        end note
        
        partition "=== ROUND 1: Initial Detection ===" {
            :ProcessRound1();
            
            :For each customer group;
            :DetectAssociation(CTSCustIDList, CustIDList);
            note right
                **Simplified Detection for Saba:**
                
                var param = new DetectAssociationParamModel {
                    CTSCustIds = ctsCustIDList,
                    CustIds = custIDList,
                    IsDevice = true,           (Always ON)
                    IsAI = true,               (Always ON)
                    IsIP = true,               (Always ON)
                    Is3MatchesLast7Days = true, (Always ON)
                    MappingCustDictionary = MappingCustDictionary (Saba!)
                };
                
                **No sport-specific configuration!**
                **No IPLast3Days / LicCustList!**
            end note
            
            if (Has GroupID?) then (yes)
                :ProcessRuleSabaGB();
                :Add to MatchProcesses[];
            endif
        }
        
        partition "=== ROUND 2: Re-processing ===" {
            :ProcessRound2();
            
            if (Has Reprocess Items?) then (yes)
                :For each reprocess item;
                :DetectAssociation (refined lists);
                note right
                    Same logic as Round 1
                    With refined customer lists
                end note
                
                if (Has GroupID?) then (yes)
                    :ProcessRuleSabaGB();
                    :Set RoundNumber = 2;
                    :Add to MatchProcesses[];
                endif
            endif
        }
        
        partition "=== COMPLETE: Save Results ===" {
            :Complete(maxSequenceID);
            
            :Merge Round 1 and Round 2;
            :Group by TransIDList;
            :Assign Sequential GroupID;
            note right
                Same logic as standard:
                - Merge results
                - Remove duplicates
                - Assign 1, 2, 3, ...
            end note
            
            if (Has Results?) then (yes)
                :CompleteTransRuleSabaGB();
                :Call SP: CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_Complete;
                note right
                    **SP Name:** CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_Complete
                    
                    **Operations:**
                    1. INSERT/UPDATE MatchMonitorDetails
                    2. UPDATE Staging GroupID
                    3. INSERT MatchMonitor
                    
                    **Tables:**
                    - MatchMonitorDetails (main results)
                    - MatchMonitor (summary)
                    - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSaba[Live/NonLive]
                end note
                
                :Mark Staging as Processed;
                note right
                    UPDATE MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSaba[Live/NonLive]
                    SET GroupID = TargetGroupID
                    WHERE TransID IN (TransIDList)
                end note
            endif
        }
        
        :WriteLogSentryIfError();
        :Sleep(100ms);
    }
    
    :Wait for All Threads;
    
    :CleanTransRuleSabaGB(isLive, maxSequenceID);
    :Call SP: CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_StagingClean;
    note right
        **SP Name:** CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_StagingClean
        
        **Clean-up Logic:**
        - Remove processed transactions
        - Keep last TimeStep transactions
        - Update SystemParameter (162 for Live, 163 for NonLive)
        
        **Tables:**
        - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSaba[Live/NonLive]
        - SystemParameter
    end note
    
else (no)
    :No matches to process;
endif

:Return Success;

stop

note right
    ===================================================
    SABA GROUP BETTING COMPLETE
    ===================================================
    
    **Key Saba Features:**
    
    1. ✅ MappingCustDictionary
       - Maps Saba CustID to CTS CTSCustID
       - Created from CTSCustomerList
       - Passed to association detection
    
    2. ✅ Simplified Detection
       - All criteria always enabled
       - No sport-specific settings
       - No IPLast3Days
    
    3. ✅ Saba-Specific Tables
       - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaLive
       - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaNonLive
       - MatchMonitorDetails (Reason = 0)
    
    4. ✅ Stored Procedures
       - CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_Get
       - CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_Complete
       - CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_StagingClean
    
    **Same as Standard:**
    - 2-round detection
    - Parallel processing
    - Merge and complete flow
    - Clean-up logic
    
    **Complexity:**
    - Simpler than standard (no sport config)
    - But has unique mapping requirement
end note

@enduml
